            . I am a carpenter. I was in the buildings near the saw-pit; I saw the prisoner take the coat from the saw-pit, and put it under his arm; I threw up the sash and bid him let the coat alone; then he ran away with it; I cried, Stop thief! and he dropped it about one hundred yards off; he was never out of my sight till he was taken.</p>
               <p>[The coat produced and deposed to by the prosecutor.]</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I was running after a mad bullock, and saw the coat lie in the road; I took it up and laid it down again, and they cried, Stop thief!</p>
